@* An <ErrorBoundary> whose content reads a COMPUTED. The computed refreshes from inside
   flush()/checkDirty(), BEFORE the binding that reads it runs, so the boundary's guard never sees
   the throw -- and Blazor's boundary DOES catch it. Refused rather than shipped as a guard that
   is not one. Decision 164. *@
<div id="wrap"><ErrorBoundary><ChildContent><p id="in">@Label</p></ChildContent><ErrorContent><p id="err">@context.Message</p></ErrorContent></ErrorBoundary></div>

@code {
    private int n = 0;

    private string Label => Risky();

    private string Risky()
    {
        if (n > 0) throw new InvalidOperationException("boom");
        return "ok";
    }
}
